Trim the @aubergine{1} and slice into 1cm thick rounds. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Preheat your #grill{} to high. Heat a drizzle of @oil{2%tsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the onion, pepper and @British beef mince{120%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until soft and golden, ~{6-7%mins}. Add the @dried oregano{1%tsp}, @tomato puree{15%g}, @ground cinnamon{1%tsp} and half the garlic. Cook for ~{1%min} more.

> MOD Step 2: If you've decided to add beef mince to your meal, add the beef mince with the onion and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Next, stir in the @red split lentils{50%g}, @Worcester sauce{7.5%ml}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @finely chopped tomatoes{1%400g can}. Add the @water{100%ml} and @sugar{1%tsp}. Stir, bring to the boil, lower the heat to medium and simmer until the lentils are soft (but still have a slight bite to them), ~{20-25%mins}. If the sauce gets too dry, just add a splash of water.

Meanwhile, lay the aubergine slices on a #baking tray{} in a single layer and drizzle over a good glug of @olive oil{2%tsp}. Season with salt and pepper. Grill until browned and soft, about ~{8-9%mins} on each side.

> TIP: Keep an eye on them to make sure they don't burn. If they aren't soft after this time, just leave them under your grill for another 2-3 mins.

Remove and set aside.

In a #small bowl{}, mix the remaining @garlic clove{1}(grated) with the olive oil. Cut the @ciabatta{1} in half (as though making a sandwich) and smear the garlic oil over the cut side. When the tomato sauce is ready, transfer the sauce to an #ovenproof dish{}. Layer over the aubergine slices. Dollop over the @creme fraiche{75%g} and then spread it out evenly across the top.

Sprinkle the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} over the moussaka and season with pepper. Grill until the cheese is golden and bubbling, about ~{5-6%mins}. Remove from the grill, pop the garlic bread under the grill and toast until golden, ~{2-3%mins}.

Serve the moussaka in #bowls{}. Add a handful of @wild rocket{20%g} alongside and drizzle with olive oil. Serve with the cheat's garlic bread and enjoy!